<h1>Diagnostics</h1>

<p>This is a overview of the current state of this Gitorious
setup.</p>

<h2>Summary<h2>

<p>Is everything ok? <%= @overall_healthy %></p>


<h2>Core functionality</h2>

<table>
  <tr><td>Can 'git clone | pull | push' to myself locally?</td><td> <%= @queues_up %></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Queues are working?</td><td> <%= @git_operations_work %></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ultrasphinx indexing working?</td><td> <%= @indexing_works %></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ultrasphinx search queries working?</td><td> <%= @search_works %></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Git user and its permissions are present and correct?</td><td><%= @git_user_ok %></td></tr>
  <tr><td>At least one Gitorious admin account exists?</td><td><%= @gitorious_admin_account_present %></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Repository directories present and correct perms?</td><td><%= @repo_dir_ok %></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Tarball cache and work directories present and correct perms?</td><td><%= @tarball_dirs_ok %></td></tr>
</table>


<h2>Services and daemons</h2>

<table>
  <tr><td> git-daemon is up?</td><td><%= @git_daemon_up %></td></tr>
  <tr><td> gitorious-poller is up?</td><td><%= @poller_up %></td></tr>
  <tr><td> Mysql is up?</td><td> <%= @mysql_up  %></td></tr>
  <tr><td> Ultrasphinx is up?</td><td> <%= @ultrasphinx_up %></td></tr>
  <tr><td> Queue service (active mq etc) is up?</td><td><%= @queue_service_up %></td></tr>
  <tr><td> Memcached is up?</td><td> <%= @memcached_up %></td></tr>
  <tr><td> Sendmail is up?</td><td> <%= @sendmail_up %></td></tr>
</table>


<h2>Host system health</h2>

<table>
  <tr><td> More than 90% disk space free?</td><td><%= @over_90_percent_disk_free %></td></tr>
  <tr><td> More than 90% RAM free?</td><td><%= @over_90_percent_RAM_free %></td></tr>
</table>

<h3>free -m</h3>
<pre>
<%= @free_output %>
</pre>

<h3>vmstat</h3>
<pre>
<%= @vmstat_output %>
</pre>

<h3>df -h</h3>
<pre>
<%= @df_output %>
</pre>


<h2>How to keep tabs on this</h2>

<p>An go/no-go summary of the system is available at a separate
<%= link_to "summary url", :action => "summary" %>. This can be pinged
regularly from an external monitoring service to keep tabs on the
status of this Gitorious installation. If everything is ok then it
will respond "OK". If not, it will respond with a 500 error code.</p>
